y]]'' \n| December 25\n| [[Mac Alejandre]] and Rico Gutierrez\n| [[Ramon \"Bong\" Revilla, Jr.]], [[Phillip Salvador]], [[Robert Villar]], [[Rhian Ramos]], [[Iza Calzado]], [[Geoff Eigenmann]]\n| [[Fantasy]]\n| Imus Productions\n|}\n\n==2010==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \"toccolours sortable\" style=\"width:97%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Title\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Release date\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Director\n! style=\"width:30%;\"|Cast\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Genre(s)\n! style=\"width:15%;\"|Associated film production\n|-\n| ''[[Working Girls (2010 film)|Working Girls]]'' \n| April 21\n| [[Jose Javier Reyes]]\n| [[Eugene Domingo]], [[Ruffa Gutierrez]], [[Iza Calzado]], [[Eula Valdez]], [[Jennylyn Mercado]], [[Cristine Reyes]], [[Bianca King]]\n| [[Comedy]]\n| [[Viva Films]], Unitel\n|-\n| ''[[You to Me Are Everything (film)|You to Me Are Everything]]'' \n| May 5\n| [[Mark A. Reyes]]\n| [[Dingdong Dantes]], [[Marian Rivera]]\n| [[Romantic comedy]]\n| [[Regal Entertainment]]\n|-\n| ''[[In Your Eyes (2010 film)|In Your Eyes]]'' \n| August 18\n| [[Mac Alejandre]]\n| [[Claudine Barretto]], [[Anne Curtis]], [[Richard Gutierrez]]\n| [[Drama]], [[Romance film|Romance]]\n| [[Viva Films]]\n|-\n| ''[[Si Agimat at si Enteng Kabisote]]'' \n| December 25\n| Tony Y. Reyes\n| [[Bong Revilla]], [[Vic Sotto]], [[Jillian Ward]], [[Sam Pinto]], [[Gwen Zamora]]\n| [[Action (fiction)|Action]], [[Adventure film|Adventure]]\n| Imus Productions, [[M-Zet Productions]], [[APT Entertainment]], [[OctoArts Films]]\n|}\n\n==2011==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \"toccolours sortable\" style=\"width:97%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Title\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Release date\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Director\n! style=\"width:30%;\"|Cast\n! style=\"width:10%;\"|Genre(s)\n! style=\"width:15%;\"|Associated film production\n|-\n| ''[[My Valentine Girls]]''  \n| February 9\n| Dominic Zapata, Andoy Ranay and Chris Martinez\n| [[Richard Gutierrez]], [[Jillian Ward]], 