ord.edu/news/2004/march3/romanov-33.html Scientists Reopen Czar Mystery]\n*[http://www.romanov-memorial.com/ Ipatiev House&nbsp;\u2014 Romanov Memorial] detailed site on the historical context, circumstances and drama surrounding the Romanov's execution\n*{{in lang|ru}} [http://gatchino.com/literatura/sokolov_n_a/ The Murder of Russia's Imperial Family], Nicolay Sokolov. Investigation of execution of the Romanovs in 1918.\n*{{in lang|ru}} [http://gatchina3000.ru/literatura/radzinski_e/ Nikolay II&nbsp;\u2014 Life and Death], Edvard Radzinski. Later published in English as ''The Last Czar: the Life and Death of Nicholas II''.\n*{{in lang|ru}} [http://az.lib.ru/w/witte_s_j/text_0040.shtml Memoirs: The reign of Nicholas II 1\u201312] [http://az.lib.ru/w/witte_s_j/text_0050.shtml 13\u201333] [http://az.lib.ru/w/witte_s_j/text_0060.shtml 34\u201345] [http://az.lib.ru/w/witte_s_j/text_0070.shtml 46\u201352] (incomplete), [[Sergei Witte]]. It was originally published in 1922 in [[Berlin]]. No complete English translations are available yet.\n*[http://www.pravmir.com/article_101.html New Russian Martyrs. Czar Nicholas and His Family]. A story of life, canonisation. Photoalbum.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070208191424/http://www.kingandwilson.com/ Russian History Magazine] Articles about the Romanovs from Atlantis magazine.\n*[http://www.smithsonianmag.com/people-places/Resurrecting-the-Czar.html Resurrecting the Czar] \u2013 November 2010 (''Smithsonian'' magazine)\n* [http://diaryrh.ru/historical-photos/the-coronation-of-nicholas-ii The coronation of Emperor Nicholas II. 26 (14, old style), may, 1896. Historical photos.]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Romanov|House of Holstein-Gottorp-Romanov]]|18 May|1868|17 July|1918|[[House of Oldenburg]]}}\n{{S-reg|}}\n{{S-bef|rows=2|before=[[Alexander III of Russia|Alexander III]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Emperor of Russia]]|years=1894\u20131917}}\n{{S-non|reason=Monarchy abolished}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Grand Duke of Finland]]|years=1894\u20131917}}\n{{S-vac|next=[[Prince Frederick Charles of Hesse|Frederick Charles]]|as=king-elect}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{S-pre|}}\n{{S-new|loss|reason=Empire abolished}}\n{{S-tul|title=[[Emperor of Russia]]|years=1917|reason=[[February Revolution|Empire abolished in 1917]]}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Grand Duke Nikolai Nikolaevich of Russia (1856\u20131929)|Nikolai Nikolaevich]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Russian emperors}}\n{{Russian grand dukes}}\n{{Supreme Commanders of the Russian Army during WWI}}\n{{Russian Revolution 1917}}\n{{Pretenders to the Russian throne since 1917}}\n{{Murder of the Romanovs}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nicholas 02}}\n[[Category:Nicholas II of Russia| ]]\n[[Category:1868 births]]\n[[Category:1918 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Russian monarchs]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian monarchs]]\n[[Category:19th-century Polish monarchs]]\n[[Category:20th-century Polish monarchs]]\n[[Category:20th-century Christian saints]]\n[[Category:British field marshals]]\n[[Category:Burials at Peter and Paul Cathedral]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Russia]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox people executed by the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Executed monarchs]]\n[[Category:House of Romanov]]\n[[Category:Leaders ousted by a coup]]\n[[Category:Monarchs who abdicated]]\n[[Category:Murdered Russian monarchs]]\n[[Category:Assassinations in Russia]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox monarchs]]\n[[Category:Hague Conventions of 1899 and 1907]]\n[[Category:Executed people from Saint Petersburg]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of St. Andrew]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of St. Alexander Nevsky]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of the White Eagle (Russia)]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of St. Anna, 1st class]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Saint Stanislaus (Russian), 1st class]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of St. Vladimir, 4th class]]\n[[Category:Grand Crosses 