 (film)|Changing Partners]]''\n|Alex\n|-\n|[[Empoy Marquez]]\n|''[[Kita Kita]]''\n|Tonyo\n|-\n|Sandino Martin\n|''[[Changing Partners (film)|Changing Partners]]''\n|Cris\n|-\n|Justine Samson\n|''Balangiga: Howling Wilderness''\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=11 style=\"text-align:center\" | '''[[42nd Gawad Urian Awards|2018]]'''<br /><small>(42nd)</small>\n|- style=\"background:#ABCDEF\"\n|'''[[Eddie Garcia]]'''\n|'''''ML'''''\n|Colonel\n|-\n|[[Carlo Aquino]]\n|''[[Meet Me in St. Gallen]]''\n|Jesse\n|-\n|[[Christian Bables]]\n|''[[Signal Rock]]''\n|Intoy\n|-\n|[[Dingdong Dantes]]\n|[[Sid & Aya: Not a Love Story|Sid & Aya]]\n|Sid\n|-\n|[[Ketchup Eusebio]]\n|''Mamang''\n|Ferdie\n|-\n|[[Eddie Garcia]]\n|''Hintayan ng Langit''\n|Manolo\n|-\n|Miyuki Kamimura\n|''Tanabata\u2019s Wife''\n|\n|-\n|Tony Labrusca\n|''ML''\n|Carlo\n|-\n|Victor Neri\n|''A Short History of a Few Bad Things''\n|Felix Tarongoy\n|-\n|[[Dante Rivero]]\n|''Kung Paano Hinihintay ang Dapithapon''\n|Bene\n|}\n\n==Superlatives==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!width=\"270\"|[[wikt:superlative|Superlative]]\n!colspan=\"2\" width=\"270\"|Best Actor\n|-\n||Actor with most awards\n|[[Phillip Salvador]]<br />[[Richard Gomez]]\n|3\n|-\n|Actor with most nominations\n|[[Christopher de Leon]]\n|13\n|-\n|Oldest Winner\n|[[Eddie Garcia]]\n|90\n|-\n|Oldest Nominee\n|[[Eddie Garcia]]\n|90\n|-\n|Youngest Winner\n|[[Jiro Manio]]\n|12\n|-\n|Youngest Nominee\n|[[Jiro Manio]]\n|12\n|}\n\n==Multiple awards for Best Actor==\n;Three awards \n*[[Richard Gomez]]\n*[[Phillip Salvador]]\n\n;Two awards\n*[[Eddie Garcia]]\n*[[Raymond Bagatsing]]\n*[[Christopher de Leon]]\n*[[Sid Lucero]]\n*[[Vic Silayan]]\n*[[Joel Torre]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Gawad Urian}}\n\n[[Category:Film awards for lead actor]]\n[[Category:Philippine film awards]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1976]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = [[Gawad Urian]] for Best Actor\n| description    = Pinakamahusay na Pangunahing Aktor (Best Performance by an Actor in a Leading Role)\n| presenter      = Manunuri ng Pelikulang Pilipino\n| country        = [[Philippines]]\n| year           = 1977\n| holder         = [[Paolo Ballesteros]]<br />''[[Die Beautiful]]'' <small>(2016)</small>\n| website        = http://www.manunuri.com\n}}\nThe '''Gawad Urian Best Actor''', (officially, the '''''Pinakamahusay na Pangunahing Aktor''''') is a movie award given by the ''Manunuri ng Pelikulang Pilipino'' (Filipino Film Critics) to [[lead actor]]s in a Philippine movie.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000270/| title=Gawad Urian | publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]  | accessdate=July 15, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.manunuri.com/| title=Manunuri ng Pelikulang Pilipino| publisher=| accessdate=July 15, 2015| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927170124/http://www.manunuri.com/| archive-date=September 27, 2015| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Winners and nominees==\nIn the lists below, the winner of the award for each year is shown first, followed by the other nominees.\n\n===1970s===\n[[File:Dolphy.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Dolphy]] was nominated for Gawad Best Actor in 1979 and 2001]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:80%\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#ABCDEF\"\n! width=\"8%\" | Year\n! width=\"19%\" | Actor\n! width=\"19%\" | Film\n! width=\"19%\" | Role\n|-\n| rowspan=6 style=\"text-align:center\" | '''[[1st Gawad Urian Awards|1976]]'''<br /><small>(1st)</small>\n|- style=\"background:#ABCDEF\"\n| '''[[Vic Silayan]]'''\n| '''''Ligaw na Bulaklak'''''\n| \n|-\n| Robert Arevalo\n| ''Divorce: Pilipino Style''\n|  \n|-\n| [[Christopher de Leon]]\n| ''[[Ganito Kami Noon, Paano Kayo Ngayon ]]''\n| Nicolas \"Kulas\" Ocampo\n|-\n| [[Bembol Roco]]\n| ''Lunes, Martes, Miyerkules, Huwebes, Biyernes, Sabado, Linggo''\n|\n|-\n| [[Tommy Abuel]]\n| ''Putik ka man, Sa Alabok Magbalik''\n| \n |-\n| rowspan=6 style=\"text-align:center\" | '''[[2nd Gawad Urian Awards|1977]]'''<br /><small>(2nd)<