le]]''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |[[Malou Santos]], [[Charo Santos-Concio]], and Trina Dayrit\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |[[Star Cinema]]\n|rowspan=3|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1996 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1996\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''Emong Salvacion: Humanda Ka...Oras Mo Na!'' <small>(2nd)</small>|| ||[[Regal Films]]\n|-\n|''Trudis Liit'' <small>(3rd)</small>|| ||RJ Films\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=3|1997 <br /><small>[[1997 Metro Manila Film Festival|(23rd)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''Nasaan ang Puso?''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |MaQ Productions\n|rowspan=3|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1997 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1997\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''Babae'' <small>(2nd)</small>||||GEM\n|-\n|''Magic Kingdom'' <small>(3rd)</small>||||[[Viva Films]] and Neo Films\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=3|1998 <br /><small>[[1998 Metro Manila Film Festival|(24th)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''[[Jos\u00e9 Rizal (film)|Jos\u00e9 Rizal]]''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |[[GMA Films]]\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |Gilberto Duavit, [[Felipe Gozon]], and Menardo Jimenez\n|rowspan=3|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1998 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1998\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''Babae sa Bintana'' <small>(2nd)</small>||[[Regal Films]]||\n|-\n|''[[Puso ng Pasko]]'' <small>(3rd)</small>||[[Star Cinema]]||\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=3 |1999 <br /><small>[[1999 Metro Manila Film Festival|(25th)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''[[Muro-Ami (film)|Muro Ami]]''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |[[GMA Films]]\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | Butch Jimenez, 