!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%;\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Film\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Production Company(ies)\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Producer(s)\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2%;\"|Ref\n|-\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n<references group=\"Note\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.imdb.com/Sections/Awards/Metro_Manila_Film_Festival/ IMDB: Metro Manila Film Festival]\n*[http://mmda.gov.ph/mmff/ Official website of the Metro Manila Film Festival]\n\n{{MMFF}}\n\n[[Category:Philippine film awards]]\n[[Category:Awards for best film]]\n[[Category:Metro Manila Film Festival]]\n\n[[nl:Metro Manila Film Festival]]\n[[tl:Paligsahan ng mga Pelikula ng Kalakhang Maynila]]\n", "text_old": "{{Main|Metro Manila Film Festival}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name           = [[Metro Manila Film Festival|Metro Manila Film Festival Award]] for Best Picture\n| description    = Best Picture\n| presenter      = [[Metropolitan Manila Development Authority|MMDA]]\n| country        = [[Philippines]]\n| year           = 1975\n| holder         = ''[[Rainbow's Sunset]]'' ([[2018 Metro Manila Film Festival|2018]])\n| website        = {{url|http://www.mmda.gov.ph/mmff/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Picture''' is an award presented annually by the [[Metropolitan Manila Development Authority]] (MMDA). It was first awarded at the [[1975 Metro Manila Film Festival|1st Metro Manila Film Festival]] ceremony, held in 1975; the film ''Diligin Mo ng Hamog ang Uhaw na Lupa'' starring [[Joseph Estrada]] received the award and it is given in honor of the film that \nhas delivered an outstanding creation of the film, including directing, acting, music composing, writing, editing and other efforts put forth into a film.<ref name=\"MMFF1\">[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1975 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1975\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref> The category was first named \"Best Film\" before changing it to \"Best Picture\" in 2007. Currently, nominees and winners are determined by Executive Committees, headed by the [[Metropolitan Manila Development Authority]] Chairman and key members of the film industry.<ref>[http://www.mmda.gov.ph/mmff/ \"Official website\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121005130322/http://www.mmda.gov.ph/mmff/ |date=2012-10-05 }}. ''MMDA''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n\n{|id=\"toc\" class=\"toc plainlinks\" style= summary=\"Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Picture\"\n|-\n! Contents: __NOTOC__\n|\n'''[[#1970s|1970s]]'''{{\u00b7}}'''[[#1980s|1980s]]'''{{\u00b7}}'''[[#1990s|1990s]]'''{{\u00b7}}'''[[#2000s|2000s]]'''{{\u00b7}}'''[[#2010s|2010s]]'''{{\u00b7}}'''[[#2020s|2020s]]'''<br>\n[[#Notes|Notes]]{{\u00b7}}[[#References|References]]{{\u00b7}}[[#External links|External links]]\n|}\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:%;\"| Key\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:%;\"| Explanation\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\"| {{double-dagger}}\n|Indicates the winning film/picture\n|}\n\n===1970s===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" background: #f6e39c;\n|- style=\"background:#bebebe;\"\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%;\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Film\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Production Company(ies)\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Producer(s)\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2%;\"|Ref\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=2|1975 <br /><small>[[1975 Metro Manila Film Festival|(1st)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''Diligin Mo ng Hamog ang Uhaw na Lupa''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | JE Production, Inc\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | Joseph Ejercito\n|rowspan=2|<ref name=\"MMFF1\" />\n|-\n|''Batu-Bato sa Langit'' <small>(3rd)</small> || NV Productions ||\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=2 |1976 <br /><small>[[1976 Metro Manila Film Festival|(2nd)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''[[Ganito Kami Noon, Paano Kayo Ngayon]]''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |Hemisphere\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |Dennis Juban\n|rowspan=2|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1976 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1976\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Minsa'y isang Gamu-gamo]]'' || Premiere Productions||Digna Santiago\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" |1977 <br /><small>[[1977 Metro Manila Film Festival|(3rd)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''Burlesk Queen''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | Ian Films\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | Romy Ching\n|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1977 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1977\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" |1978 <br /><small>[[1978 Metro Manila Film Festival|(4th)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''Atsay''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | Ian Films\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | Romy Ching\n|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1978 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1978\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=2|1979 <br /><small>[[1979 Metro Manila Film Festival|(5th)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''Kasal-kasalan, Bahay-bahayan''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | HPS Films\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" | Hermogenes P. Santiago\n|rowspan=2|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1979 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1979\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Ina ka ng Anak Mo]]''|| ||Lourdes A. Marquez <small>(Executive producer)</small>\n|}\n\n===1980s===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" background: #f6e39c;\n|- style=\"background:#bebebe;\"\n!scope=\"