a Film Festival|(30th)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''[[Mano Po III: My Love]]''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |[[Regal Films]]\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |Roselle Monteverde-Teo\n|rowspan=3|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/2004 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:2004\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Panaghoy sa Suba]]'' <small>(2nd)</small>||CM Films Inc.||[[Cesar Montano]]\n|-\n|''[[Aishite Imasu 1941: Mahal Kita]]'' <small>(3rd)</small>||[[Regal Films]] and BASFILM Productions||\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=3|2005 <br /><small>[[2005 Metro Manila Film Festival|(31st)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |''[[Blue Moon (2006 film)|Blue Moon]]''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |[[Regal Films]]\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |Roselle Monteverde-Teo\n|rowspan=3|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/2005 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:2005\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Exodus: Tales from the Enchanted Kingdom]]'' <small>(2nd)</small>||Imus Productions and Media Asia Distribution||Imus Productions and Reality Entertainment\n|-\n|''[[Kutob]]'' <small>(3rd)</small>||Canary Films||\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center\" rowspan=3 |2006 <br /><small>[[2006 Metro Manila Film Festival|(32nd)]] </small>\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\"|''[[Enteng Kabisote 3: Okay Ka, Fairy Ko: The Legend Goes On and On and On]]''{{double dagger|alt=Award winner}}\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |[[OctoArts Films]] and M-Zet Productions\n| style=\"background:#FAEB86\" |Orly R. Ilacad\n|rowspan=3|<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/2006 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:2006\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Kasal, Kasali, Kasalo]]'' <small>(2nd)</small>|| [[Star Cinema]]||\n|-\n|''[[Shake, Rattle & Roll 8]]'' <small>(3rd)</small>||[[Regal Films]]||Roselle Monteverde-Teo\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" styl