a Nawala''\n| Lio\n|-\n| [[James Reid (actor)|James Reid]]\n| ''[[Never Not Love You]]''\n| Gio Smith \n|-\n| [[Mon Confiado]]\n| ''El Peste''\n| Abner\n|-\n| Ybes Bagadiong\n| ''Dog Days''\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n==Superlatives==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!width=\"270\"|[[wikt:superlative|Superlative]]\n!colspan=\"2\" width=\"270\"|Best Actor\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Actor with most awards\n|[[Eddie Garcia]]\n|6\n|-\n|[[Joseph Estrada]]<br />[[Fernando Poe Jr.]]<br />[[Christopher De Leon]]\n|5\n|-\n|Actor with most nominations\n|[[Fernando Poe Jr.]]\n|15\n|-\n|Oldest winner\n|[[Eddie Garcia]]\n|89\n|-\n|Oldest nominee\n|[[Eddie Garcia]]\n|89\n|-\n|Youngest winner\n|[[Christopher De Leon]]\n|19\n|-\n|Youngest nominee\n|[[Cogie Domingo]]\n|16\n|}\n\n*[[Eddie Garcia]] won the award more than any actors with six wins. [[Joseph Estrada]], [[Fernando Poe Jr.]] and [[Christopher De Leon]] have also won the award five times. All four of them are inducted to the FAMAS Hall of Fame.\n*Three actors have won the award consecutively. They are [[Christopher De Leon]] (in 1991 and 1992), [[Allen Dizon]] (in 2010 and 2011), and [[ER Ejercito]] (in 2012, 2013 and 2014)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060717171103/http://www.freewebs.com/famas_awards/ The Unofficial Website of the Filipino Academy of Movie Arts and Sciences]\n*[https://www.imdb.com/Sections/Awards/FAMAS_Awards/ FAMAS Awards]\n\n{{FAMAS Awards}}\n\n[[Category:FAMAS Award|Best Actor]]\n[[Category: Film awards for lead actor]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = [[Filipino Academy of Movie Arts and Sciences Award|FAMAS Award]] for Best Actor\n| description    = Best Performance by an Actor in a Leading Role\n| presenter      = [[Filipino Academy of Movie Arts and Sciences Award]]\n| country        = [[Philippines]]\n| year           = 1952 \n| holder         = [[Allen Dizon]]<br />''Bomba'' ([[2017 FAMAS Awards|2017]])\n| website        = \n}}\n\nThe '''FAMAS Award for Best Actor''' is one of the [[FAMAS Award]]s given to people working in the [[film|motion picture]] industry by the [[Filipino Academy of Movie Arts and Sciences Award]], which are voted on by [[Palanca Award]]-winning writers and movie columnists and writers within the industry.\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n[[File:Joseph Estrada 1998.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Joseph Estrada]] has won the award five times from thirteen nominations for his roles in 1962's ''Markang Rehas'', 1964's ''Geron Busabos: Ang Batang Quiapo'', 1966's ''Ito ang Pilipino'', 1969's ''Dugo ng Bayani'' and 1981's ''Kumander Alibasbas''.]]\n[[File:George Nader November 1956.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[George Nader]] has been nominated for his role in 1963's ''Zigzag''.]]\n[[File:Dolphy.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Dolphy]] has won once from nine nominations for his role in 1977's ''Omeng Santanasia''.]]\n\n\n[[File:Ramon Bong Revilla.JPG|right|thumb|150px|[[Bong Revilla]] has won once from ten nominations for his role in 1993's ''Relax Ka Lang, Sagot Kita''.]]\n[[File:Robin Padilla.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Robin Padilla]] has won once from four nominations for his role in 2005's ''[[La Visa Loca]]''.]]\n[[File:Gabby Concepcion at the KC Concepcion Live US Concert Tour, November 2010.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Gabby Concepcion]] has been nominated twice for his roles in 1991's ''Una Kang Naging Akin'' and 2009's ''[[I Love You, Goodbye (film)|I Love You, Goodbye]]''.]]\n[[File:Piolo Pascual at the Star Magic Concert Tour in Ontario, CA, June 2009.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Piolo Pascual]] has won once from six nominations for his role in 2004's ''[[Milan (2004 film)|Milan]]''.]]\n[[File:Ryan Agoncillo (2008).jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Ryan Agoncillo]] has been nominated once for his role in 2006's ''Umaaraw, Umuulan''.]]\n[[File:John Lloyd Cruz at ABS-CBN Talent Center, May 2010.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[John Lloyd Cruz]] has won once from seven nominations for his role in 2010's ''[[Miss You like Crazy (film)|Miss You Like Crazy]]''.]]\n[[File:John Estrada.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[John Estrada]] has been nominated once for his role in 2008's ''[[Caregiver (film)|Caregiver]]''.]]\n[[File:Derek Ramsay at the KC Concepcion Live Concert Press Conference, November 2010.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Derek Ramsay]] has been nominated thrice for his roles in 2011's ''[[No Other Woman]]'', 2012's ''[[A Secret Affair]]'' and 2014's ''[[English Only, Please]]''.]]\n[[File:Dingdong Dantes at the Eat Bulaga! Press Conference, July 2008.JPG|right|thumb|150px|[[Dingdong Dantes]] has been nominated thrice for his roles in 2011's ''[[Segunda Mano]]'', 2012's ''[[One More Try (film)|One More Try]]'' and 2013's ''[[She's the One (2013 film)|She's the One]]''.]]\n[[File:Xian Lim at the Star Magic Concert Tour in Ontario, CA, June 2009.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Xian Lim]] has been nominated once for his role in 2013's ''[[Bakit Hindi Ka Crush ng Crush Mo?]]''.]]\n[[File:Gerald Anderson by Ronn Tan, April 2010.png|right|thumb|150px|[[Gerald Anderson]] has been nominated once for his role in 2013's ''[[On the Job (2013 film)|On the Job]]''.]]\nThe list may be incomplete such as some of the names of the nominees and the roles portrayed especially during the early years of FAMAS Awards.\n\nIn the lists below, the winner of the award for each year is shown first, followed by the other nominees. \n\n*Note \u2013 The year indicates the awards for the films of that year when those films were originally released. Please refer to the Academy Awards how they label the awards for the films original release date and not the awards ceremony date. \n\u2021 \u2013 indicates the winner\n\n\u2020 \u2013 indicates the performance was also nominated for the [[Academy Award]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:80%\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#bebebe\"\n! width=\"8%\" | Year\n! width=\"18%\" | Actor\n! width=\"18%\" | Film\n! width=\"18%\" | Role\n|-|-\n| rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center\" | '''[[1s